    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">
            {{title}}
        </h1>

        <p>All designs so far for One Login work. These are likely to change over time, but this index page will keep track of all the designs and link to them.</p>



        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            Phase 1: before launch
        </h2>

        <p>Team discussions suggest we may not be considering any notifications upfront, due to what we can provide may be too vague. For example, Jobseekers cannot go and create a One login account beforehand or may not want to, therefore, does it make sense to just be clear one it has happened rather than confuse people before it has?</p>

        <p>Old designs have been added to <a href="#not-moving-forward">concepts we're not moving forward with</a>.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            Phase 2: Launched
        </h2>

        <ul class="govuk-list">
            <li>
                <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="/onelogin/create">Create account page</a> 
            </li>
            <li>
                <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="/onelogin/login_first_time">How you sign in has changed message</a> - the first time a jobseeker tries to sign in after the switch
            </li>
            <li>
                <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="/onelogin/login_second_time">New jobseeker sign in page</a> - every time a jobseeker tries to sign in after the initial switch message
            </li>
            <li>
                <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="/onelogin/emails/launch">Notify email telling people about change</a> 
            </li>
            <li>
                <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="/onelogin/profile">Banner on profile</a> - how long and in what circumstances should this be visible?
            </li>
        </ul>
       

